# Git commit

When executing or suggesting `git commit` in this repository:

- Use ONLY: `git commit -m "commit message"`.
- Do NOT use `--trailer` or any option that adds "Co-authored-by" or similar.
- The repository has a single author (the human owner). No agent or tool may appear as co-author in commits.
